page.title: 09 BEBINGTON HOUSING
page.content: The oldest and most tigthly packed housing is the pre-1914 clustering of houses by the junction of Old Chester Rd and Kings Lane. Here some large Victorian houses have been converted into commercial premises, and there are terraces in Woodburn Boulevard. It is clearly possible to visualise this as being the only{"built up"}part of the whole area in 1900. During the interim period, with the development of more suburbs whith semi-detached{ {housing}rather than terracing the area developed in this way. Only here and there, along Kings Rd specially, are there houses which are clearly of the post 1945 period. The large{Bebington {Cemetary}was developed early in the century and covers a significant amount of land.It is hardly surprising that there are a large number of schools built to serve the population.
